## 3.2.1.1 Idealized optimal execution problem

### Purpose

This subsection formalizes the trading objective used to derive the pre-trade cost model.

### Setup / formulation

The trader maximizes expected fundamental P&L plus terminal alpha:

$$
\sup_Q
\mathbb{E}
\left[
\tilde{\alpha}^r Q_T
+
\int_0^T Q_t dS_t
-
\int_0^T I_t dQ_t
-
\frac{1}{2}[I,Q]_T
\right].
$$

The impact process follows the generalized OW model:

$$
dI_t = -\beta_t I_t dt + \lambda_t dQ_t.
$$

### Main result

The objective decomposes trading value into:

- alpha payoff,
- unperturbed price exposure,
- impact cost,
- quadratic variation correction.

### Interpretation

The use of fundamental P&L avoids rewarding a strategy for mechanically inflating accounting P&L through its own impact.

