$$

Equivalently, the pre-trade cost curve is approximately quadratic:

$$
\text{Cost}(Q_T) \approx \frac{1}{2}\Lambda_T Q_T^2.
$$

### Main result

The execution desk can expose a simple scalar cost model while maintaining a richer intraday execution model internally.

### Interpretation

This is analogous to implied volatility in options. A complex market object is compressed into a useful trading parameter.

