## 3.2.2.1 Alpha latency

### Purpose

This subsection distinguishes slow execution alphas from low-latency microstructure alphas.

### Setup / formulation

Signals differ by latency and implementation layer:

- Slow intraday alpha can be included directly in the strategic execution schedule.
- Low-latency alpha is handled by tactical execution logic.

### Main result

Not all alpha belongs in the same optimization problem. Strategic alpha and tactical alpha should be modeled separately.

### Interpretation

A central optimizer can handle slowly evolving alpha. A low-latency router or smart order logic handles micro-alpha such as queue position, spread capture, or short-term order-book imbalance.

