## 3.2.3.2 Block trades and auctions

### Purpose

This subsection explains how idealized jumps in the optimal strategy relate to real execution mechanisms.

### Setup / formulation

OW-style optimizers can prescribe jumps at boundary times, especially at the start or end of the interval.

In practice, jumps may be approximated through:

- opening auction,
- closing auction,
- block trade,
- dark pool liquidity,
- accelerated schedule over a short interval.

### Main result

The mathematical optimizer may produce boundary trades that are idealized. Real implementation must respect venue liquidity and market microstructure.

### Interpretation

A prescribed jump is not necessarily an instruction to immediately sweep the book. It is a target impact adjustment that must be implemented using available liquidity mechanisms.

