## 3.4 Summary of Results

### Purpose

This section summarizes the chapter’s practitioner formulas and modeling implications.

### Setup / formulation

Important objects:

- $\Lambda_T$: pre-trade liquidity parameter,
- $\tilde{\alpha}$: implied or predicted terminal alpha,
- $\alpha_t$: intraday alpha,
- $I_t^*$: target impact,
- $\delta I_t$: tactical impact deviation,
- $C$: clean-up cost.

### Main result

The chapter’s core formulas are:

$$
Q_T = \frac{\tilde{\alpha}}{\Lambda_T}.
$$

$$
\tilde{\alpha} = \Lambda_T Q_T.
$$

$$
\frac{1}{\Lambda_T}
=
\frac{1}{\lambda_T}
+
\int_0^T
\frac{(\beta_t+\gamma_t')^2}
{\lambda_t(2\beta_t+\gamma_t')}
dt.
$$

$$
I_t^*
=
\frac{\beta_t+\gamma_t'}{2\beta_t+\gamma_t'}
(\tilde{\alpha}+\alpha_t)
-
\frac{1}{2\beta_t+\gamma_t'}\alpha_t'.
$$

$$
d\delta I_t
=
-\beta_t\delta I_t dt
+
\lambda_t d\delta Q_t.
$$

$$
\text{Deviation penalty}
=
-
\mathbb{E}
\left[
\int_0^T
\frac{2\beta_t+\gamma_t'}{2\lambda_t}
(\delta I_t)^2dt
+
\frac{1}{2\lambda_T}
(\delta I_T)^2
\right].
$$

$$
C
=
\mathbb{E}
\left[
\frac{1}{2}\tilde{\Lambda}\tilde{Q}^2
+
\frac{\tilde{\Lambda}}{\lambda_T}I_T\tilde{Q}
+
\frac{1}{2\lambda_T}
\left(
\frac{\tilde{\Lambda}}{\lambda_T}
-
1
\right)
I_T^2
\mid
\mathcal{F}_T
\right].
$$

